<subSubSection id="C359A2D369301669FF7B57F5C9E7FD3C" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="449" pageId="13" pageNumber="448" type="key">
<keyStep id="30B7E9FD6930166AFF7B57F5C9E0F96A" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">
<paragraph id="8BFCF1586930166AFF7B57F5C9E0F94D" blockId="13.[151,1436,1720,2034]" box="[151,1435,1720,1741]" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">
<keyLead id="30B2526D6930166AFF7B57F5C9E0F94D" box="[151,1435,1720,1741]" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">1. Tergites black........................................................................................ 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFCF1586930166AFF7B5798C9E0F96A" blockId="13.[151,1436,1720,2034]" box="[151,1435,1749,1770]" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">
<keyLead id="30B2526D6930166AFF7B5798C9E0F96A" box="[151,1435,1749,1770]" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">- Some tergites reddish partially or completely................................................................ 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30B7E9FD6930166AFF7B57BEC9EDF81B" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">
<paragraph id="8BFCF1586930166AFF7B57BEC9E7F8C2" blockId="13.[151,1436,1720,2034]" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">
<keyLead id="30B2526D6930166AFF7B57BEC9E7F8C2" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">
2. Macrosetae of mystax mixed black and white, longer than proboscis length. Ocellar macrosetae mainly black, in length commonly reaching to apex of antenna. Scutum with dense long black and white setae and macrosetae. Scutellum with numerous long white apical scutellar macrosetae and usually with a few long white discal scutellar setae.......... 
<taxonomicName id="4C438ADB6930166AFB375660C9E7F8C2" authority="(Loew)" authorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[1243,1436,1837,1858]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Heteropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="filicornis">
<emphasis id="B9372D4A6930166AFB375660C935F8C2" box="[1243,1358,1837,1858]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">H. filicornis</emphasis>
(Loew)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFCF1586930166AFF7B5606C9EDF81B" blockId="13.[151,1436,1720,2034]" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">
<keyLead id="30B2526D6930166AFF7B5606C9EDF81B" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">
- Mystacal setae and macrosetae mainly black. Mystax equal or shorter than length of proboscis. Ocellar setae white, equal or longer than length of scape and pedicel combined. Scutum with sparse short white and black setae. Postpronotal lobe without setae. Scutellum lacking apical scutellar macrosetae and usually lacking discal scutellar setae......... 
<taxonomicName id="4C438ADB6930166AFB3856C8C938F81A" authority="Sаkhvon &amp; Lelej, 2018" authorityName="Sаkhvon &amp; Lelej" authorityYear="2018" box="[1236,1347,1925,1946]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Heteropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hiemalis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9372D4A6930166AFB3856C8C938F81A" box="[1236,1347,1925,1946]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">H. hiemalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20490316930166AFAA556C8C9EDF81B" box="[1353,1430,1925,1947]" pageId="13" pageNumber="448" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9372D4A6930166AFAA556C8C9EDF81B" bold="true" box="[1353,1430,1925,1947]" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30B7E9FD69301669FF7B56EEC9E7FF2C" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="449" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">
<paragraph id="8BFCF1586930166AFF7B56EEC9E0F838" blockId="13.[151,1436,1720,2034]" box="[151,1435,1955,1976]" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">
<keyLead id="30B2526D6930166AFF7B56EEC9E0F838" box="[151,1435,1955,1976]" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">3. Mid tibia with a tuft of black setae in the middle............................................................. 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFCF1586930166AFF7B568DC9E0F855" blockId="13.[151,1436,1720,2034]" box="[151,1435,1984,2005]" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">
<keyLead id="30B2526D6930166AFF7B568DC9E0F855" box="[151,1435,1984,2005]" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">- Mid tibia lacking a tuft of black setae in the middle........................................................... 7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<footnote id="E858ED566930166AFF7B5690C9E0F872" box="[151,1435,2013,2034]" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">
<paragraph id="8BFCF1586930166AFF7B5690C9E0F872" blockId="13.[151,1436,1720,2034]" box="[151,1435,2013,2034]" pageId="13" pageNumber="448">4. Pulvillus are well developed and longer than length of half of claw.............................................. 5</paragraph>
</footnote>
<paragraph id="8BFCF15869331669FF7B51DAC9E7FF2C" blockId="14.[151,1436,151,700]" box="[151,1436,151,172]" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
<keyLead id="30B2526D69331669FF7B51DAC9E7FF2C" box="[151,1436,151,172]" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
- Pulvillus shorter than length of half of claw................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C438ADB69331669FB3B51DAC9E7FF2C" authority="Hermann" authorityName="Hermann" authorityYear="1906" box="[1239,1436,151,172]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Heteropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrinus">
<emphasis id="B9372D4A69331669FB3B51DAC947FF2C" box="[1239,1340,151,172]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">H. pyrinus</emphasis>
Hermann
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30B7E9FD69331669FF7B51F8C9E7FEA2" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
<paragraph id="8BFCF15869331669FF7B51F8C9E0FF4A" blockId="14.[151,1436,151,700]" box="[151,1435,181,202]" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
<keyLead id="30B2526D69331669FF7B51F8C9E0FF4A" box="[151,1435,181,202]" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">5. Mid tibia with white or pale dense setae not reaching tarsomere I............................................... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFCF15869331669FF7B519FC9E7FEA2" blockId="14.[151,1436,151,700]" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
<keyLead id="30B2526D69331669FF7B519FC9E7FEA2" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
- Mid tibia with white dense setae reaching tarsomere I–II. The tuft of black setae in the middle of mid tibia equal or shorter than length of white setae. Scutum with long dense white setae and macrosetae. Scutellum with few white apical scutellar macrosetae and numerous discal scutellar setae......................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C438ADB69331669FAEA5040C9E7FEA2" authority="Lehr" authorityName="Lehr" authorityYear="1970" box="[1286,1436,269,290]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Heteropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosus">
<emphasis id="B9372D4A69331669FAEA5040C913FEA2" box="[1286,1384,269,290]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">H. pilosus</emphasis>
Lehr
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30B7E9FD69331669FF7B5067C9E0FE17" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
<paragraph id="8BFCF15869331669FF7B5067C9EDFEDC" blockId="14.[151,1436,151,700]" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
<keyLead id="30B2526D69331669FF7B5067C9EDFEDC" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
6. Mid tibia with white dense setae and with conspicuous tuft of black setae in the middle. Scutum with short white and black setae. Scutellum with 2–4 white apical scutellar macrosetae..................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C438ADB69331669FB0D500AC9EDFEDC" authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1851" box="[1249,1430,327,348]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Heteropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatipes">
<emphasis id="B9372D4A69331669FB0D500AC922FEDC" box="[1249,1369,327,348]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">H. ornatipes</emphasis>
Loew
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFCF15869331669FF7B5028C9E0FE17" blockId="14.[151,1436,151,700]" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
<keyLead id="30B2526D69331669FF7B5028C9E0FE17" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
- The tuft of black setae in the middle of mid tibia equal to or shorter than length of pale setae. Scutum with dense short black setae. Scutellum with 2–4 (rarely 6) black apical scutellar macrosetae.............................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C438ADB69331669FB0D50CFC9E0FE17" authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1847" box="[1249,1435,386,407]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Heteropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scoparius">
<emphasis id="B9372D4A69331669FB0D50CFC925FE17" box="[1249,1374,386,407]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">H. scoparius</emphasis>
Loew
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30B7E9FD69331669FF7B50D2C9E7FE52" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
<paragraph id="8BFCF15869331669FF7B50D2C9E0FE34" blockId="14.[151,1436,151,700]" box="[151,1435,415,436]" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
<keyLead id="30B2526D69331669FF7B50D2C9E0FE34" box="[151,1435,415,436]" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">7. Stylus thin and long.................................................................................... 8</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFCF15869331669FF7B50F0C9E7FE52" blockId="14.[151,1436,151,700]" box="[151,1436,444,466]" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
<keyLead id="30B2526D69331669FF7B50F0C9E7FE52" box="[151,1436,444,466]" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
- Stylus wide and short, in length (without aristomere) equal to or more than half of postpedicel length....... 
<taxonomicName id="4C438ADB69331669FAE950F0C932FE52" authority="Sаkhvon &amp; Lelej, 2018" authorityName="Sаkhvon &amp; Lelej" authorityYear="2018" box="[1285,1353,445,466]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Heteropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ater" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9372D4A69331669FAE950F0C932FE52" box="[1285,1353,445,466]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">H. ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A204903169331669FAA350F1C9E7FE52" box="[1359,1436,444,466]" pageId="14" pageNumber="449" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9372D4A69331669FAA350F1C9E7FE52" bold="true" box="[1359,1436,444,466]" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30B7E9FD69331669FF7B5097C9E7FD3C" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
<paragraph id="8BFCF15869331669FF7B5097C9E7FDC7" blockId="14.[151,1436,151,700]" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
<keyLead id="30B2526D69331669FF7B5097C9E7FDC7" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
8. Macrosetae and setae of mystax white, with few dark brown macrosetae in lower facial margin in frontal view. Postocular macrosetae and setae white. Scutum with short sparse white setae, some dark brown. Scutellum lacking apical scutellar macrosetae. Fore tarsi, especially tarsomeres I–IV anterodorsally and posterodorsally with dense, comparably long white setae.......................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C438ADB69331669FB23537FC9E7FDC7" authority="Hermann" authorityName="Hermann" authorityYear="1906" box="[1231,1436,562,583]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Heteropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lugubris">
<emphasis id="B9372D4A69331669FB23537FC947FDC7" box="[1231,1340,562,583]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">H. lugubris</emphasis>
Hermann
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFCF15869331669FF7B5302C9E7FD3C" blockId="14.[151,1436,151,700]" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
<keyLead id="30B2526D69331669FF7B5302C9E7FD3C" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">
- Mystax with only white macrosetae and setae. Postocular macrosetae white, but setae white and black. Scutum with short sparse black setae, some of them white. Scutellum with 2 long white apical scutellar macrosetae. Fore tarsi, especially tarsomeres I–IV anterodorsally and posterodorsally with white setae comparatively dense and long posterodorsally only.............................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C438ADB69331669FB3C53EAC9E7FD3C" authority="Lehr" authorityName="Lehr" authorityYear="1970" box="[1232,1436,679,700]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Heteropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesasiaticus">
<emphasis id="B9372D4A69331669FB3C53EAC913FD3C" box="[1232,1384,679,700]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="449">H. mesasiaticus</emphasis>
Lehr
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
